15:30.829 --> 15:33.127
an elephant and four castrati.

15:33.232 --> 15:35.132
What's a castrati?

15:35.234 --> 15:37.225
I don't know,
but I'm sure it's spicy.

15:37.336 --> 15:39.804
- [Hushed] Why is that woman still living here?
- [Murmurs]

15:41.540 --> 15:44.441
Hey. You seen Apu lately?
He looks terrible.

15:44.543 --> 15:46.704
Yeah. Rumor has it
Marge threw him out.

15:46.812 --> 15:49.042
Aw, tough break.
She's a beautiful lady.

15:49.148 --> 15:51.116
You got that straight, Barn.

15:51.216 --> 15:52.911
[All]
To Marge!

15:54.386 --> 15:57.412
Moe, what do you recommend
for severe depression?

15:57.523 --> 15:59.821
Booze, booze and more booze.

15:59.925 --> 16:03.258
Huh. Nothir like a depressant
to chase the blues away.

16:03.362 --> 16:05.262
[All Muttering Agreement]

16:05.364 --> 16:10.131
Oh. Manjula and I have
not seen each other in 20 years.

16:10.235 --> 16:13.136
Two people cannot fall in love
sight unseen.

16:13.238 --> 16:15.536
Hold on there.
I'm countir on that.

16:15.641 --> 16:18.872
Well, just 24 hours
of freedom left.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.879
Actually, it's more like 12.
No. I'm so stupid.

16:21.981 --> 16:24.108
Seven. It's seven hours.

16:24.216 --> 16:26.184
You have seven hours.
See? Seven.

16:26.285 --> 16:27.980
[Sighs]

16:28.087 --> 16:31.318
## [Morosely Singing Sexy Rock]

16:37.730 --> 16:39.698
## [Ends]

16:39.798 --> 16:42.699
Come on. You shouldn't be spending
your last hours of bachelorhood...

16:42.801 --> 16:44.701
in a dump like this.

16:44.803 --> 16:46.998
You should be livir
like there's no tomorrow.

16:47.106 --> 16:49.074
And I know just the place.

16:49.174 --> 16:51.335
Ahh.

16:51.443 --> 16:54.105
Is this the life, or what?

16:54.213 --> 16:56.340
You want me
to turn on the bubbles?

16:59.985 --> 17:02.385
Which Bombay-to-Springfield
flight is she on-

17:02.488 --> 17:05.252
the 10:00, the 10:15
or the 10:30?

17:05.357 --> 17:07.257
<i>I am so terribly sorry, sir.</i>

17:07.358 --> 17:10.156
It appears that your tiger
has been sent to St. Louis.

17:10.262 --> 17:13.060
Mm-hmm. I should send you
to St. Louis!

17:13.165 --> 17:15.133
No! No, he's not won'th it.

17:15.233 --> 17:18.464
Can you please indicate
your tiger type on this chart?

17:19.905 --> 17:23.204
[Together]
Mmm, number 6.

17:25.310 --> 17:27.278
How's that fire ring coming?

17:27.378 --> 17:29.677
- Is it sacred yet?
- Almost.

17:30.783 --> 17:33.843
- [Grunting]
- Can you believe it?

17:33.952 --> 17:36.420
Tradition forbids me
even to speak to the woman...

17:36.522 --> 17:38.490
I'm about to spend
my life with.

17:38.590 --> 17:42.026
- Has the whole world gone crazy?
- Nah. Just your screwy country.

17:42.127 --> 17:46.188
[Sighs] Your old friend Apu is a lamb
being led to the slaughter.

17:46.298 --> 17:50.257
Don't worry, Apu. Someday,
you'll meet someone you really love.

17:50.369 --> 17:52.530
I am really doomed.

17:52.638 --> 17:55.072
Only the gods could
stop this wedding now.

17:55.174 --> 17:57.142
Gods, eh?

17:57.242 --> 17:59.506
[Chattering]

18:03.348 --> 18:06.044
No, no, no, no.
No pansies for me.

18:06.151 --> 18:08.119
It's the tradition in India.

18:08.220 --> 18:10.654
Yeah, all right.
It'll cover the gravy stains.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.849
- Hey!
- Tradition.

18:12.958 --> 18:15.051
Thanks for helping us out, Reverend.

18:15.160 --> 18:17.788
I know you've never performed
a Hindu ceremony.

18:17.896 --> 18:20.160
Well, Christ is Christ.

18:20.265 --> 18:22.426
Plus, I consulted
a Hindu Web site.

18:22.534 --> 18:26.095
## [Fanfare]

18:30.843 --> 18:32.538
Hello, everyone.

18:32.644 --> 18:34.942
What a happy, happy day.

18:35.047 --> 18:37.345
Wow. I wish I had an elephant.

18:37.449 --> 18:39.440
You did.
His name was Stampy.

18:39.551 --> 18:41.451
- You loved him.
- Oh, yeah.

18:43.088 --> 18:45.556
- [Squeaking]
- [Trumpeting]
- [All Gasping]

18:47.860 --> 18:49.953
Lucky mouse.

18:51.630 --> 18:53.257
- <i>##[Fanfare]</i>
- Huh?

18:58.203 --> 19:00.569
<i>[Reople Gasp]</i>

19:00.672 --> 19:02.902
Oh! Manjula?

19:03.008 --> 19:06.205
Apu. Remember me?

19:06.311 --> 19:10.077
- Obviously not.
- <i>[Crashing]</i>

19:10.182 --> 19:15.176
I am the god Ganesh!
This wedding angers me!

19:15.287 --> 19:18.256
All will die unless it is stopped.

19:19.358 --> 19:21.849
- Oh, God.
- Please! Listen to me!

19:21.960 --> 19:24.155
[Eerie Moaning]

19:24.263 --> 19:27.289
[Speaking Foreign Language]

19:27.399 --> 19:29.890
[Screams]
Stop chasing Ganesh!

19:30.002 --> 19:32.766
You're just gonna get
more wrath!

19:32.871 --> 19:36.272
- Oh. I'm afraid this is all my fault, Manjula.
- [Homer Shouting]

19:36.375 --> 19:38.343
To be perfectly honest with you...

19:38.443 --> 19:42.573
I have not exactly been looking forward
to this arranged marriage.

19:42.681 --> 19:44.581
Oh. Nor have I.

19:44.683 --> 19:48.016
Marrying a complete stranger?
It is crazy.

19:48.120 --> 19:50.680
All right.
Ganesh has been subdued.

19:50.789 --> 19:53.417
- [Whimpering] All will die.
- [Children Grunting]

19:53.525 --> 19:55.425
Resume the ceremony.

19:55.527 --> 19:59.190
Quickly, tell me. What is your favorite
movie, book and food?

19:59.298 --> 20:03.132
Uh, the answer to all three
is "fried green tomatoes."

20:03.235 --> 20:05.863
[Both Laughing]

20:05.971 --> 20:09.338
- That-That is good.
- [Clears Throat] Double-parked.

20:09.441 --> 20:11.341
Oh. I am so torn.

20:11.443 --> 20:14.810
You are clearly
so quick-witted and beautiful.

20:14.913 --> 20:17.108
And when I look in your eyes...

20:17.216 --> 20:21.346
I see that sweet little boy
who sold me my very first kiss.

20:21.453 --> 20:23.614
And I liked it.

20:23.722 --> 20:28.125
Oh. Do you think this marriage
could really work?

20:28.227 --> 20:31.162
Who knows?
We can always get divorced.

20:31.263 --> 20:34.096
Of course.
God bless America.

20:42.341 --> 20:45.742
And now, ladies and gentlemen...

20:45.844 --> 20:48.574
let me be the first
to present to you...

20:48.680 --> 20:53.481
Mr. and Mrs. Apu Nahasapeemapetilon.

20:53.585 --> 20:57.043
<i>[Cheering]</i>

20:57.155 --> 20:59.214
Aw, geez!

20:59.324 --> 21:02.782
I am no good at weddings.
I am no good at weddings.

21:02.894 --> 21:05.124
<i>##[Band]</i>

21:05.230 --> 21:09.223
## [Singing Pop Ballad
In Foreign Language]

21:17.509 --> 21:19.067
Dad, those peanuts
aren't for you.

21:19.177 --> 21:21.839
- They're for the elephant.
- Screw him!

21:21.947 --> 21:23.915
[Screams]
Put me down!

21:24.016 --> 21:25.779
Ganesh commands you!
[Whimpering]

21:25.884 --> 21:28.944
Well, so far, so good.
Don't you think?

21:29.054 --> 21:31.682
I cannot wait
to show you our apartment.

21:31.790 --> 21:34.315
Apartment?
Oh, no. No, no.

21:34.426 --> 21:37.589
You must buy me a house.
And you're getting a haircut.

21:37.696 --> 21:39.391
Oh.

21:39.498 --> 21:42.990
- Got you.
- Oh. [Laughing]

21:43.101 --> 21:45.661
- ## [Continues]
- [Whimpering] Come on, elephant!

21:45.771 --> 21:48.740
Stop!
[Yelping, Groaning]

21:52.010 --> 21:53.807
Hey, everybody's upside-down.

21:53.979 --> 21:56.812
[Giggling]

21:56.915 --> 21:59.509
Look at that. Well.

22:39.624 --> 22:42.286
- [Murmuring]
- Shh!

